                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14941272" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 2 Oct 2015 15:35:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached trivial patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14941274" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 2 Oct 2015 15:37:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As a side note, it seems the pig test were, for some reason, using &lt;tt&gt;offheap_objects&lt;/tt&gt; so the patch also change that, which should hopefully the tests current failures.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14945432" author="aweisberg" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2015 17:37:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The code changes look fine, but is there a branch where this is being tested by cassci? Are there dtests requesting this option?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14945466" author="aweisberg" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2015 17:59:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created a branch for cassci to run it. Will report back.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14945824" author="aweisberg" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2015 21:16:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/aweisberg/job/aweisberg-C-10437-dtest/1/#showFailuresLink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtests&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/aweisberg/job/aweisberg-C-10437-testall/1/#showFailuresLink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;utests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I went through the results and it seems to match trunk for the most part. None of the failures looked related to me. I kicked off another test-all and dtest just to see what repeats and what doesn&apos;t. Otherwise +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14945825" author="aweisberg" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2015 21:17:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, actually what is the doc impact here? Has that been taken care of?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14946527" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2015 08:55:48 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I kicked off another test-all and dtest just to see what repeats and what doesn&apos;t. Otherwise +1.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given the nature of the patch, I&apos;m reasonably confident that it can&apos;t break anything that wasn&apos;t already broken so took the liberty to commit without waiting on those repeated test results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;what is the doc impact here? Has that been taken care of?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To the best of my knowledge, as far as the open-source goes, this option isn&apos;t documented anywhere outside the &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.yaml&lt;/tt&gt; file, and the patch does update that part (as well as notify the change in the &lt;tt&gt;NEWS&lt;/tt&gt; file for upgraders).  External documentations might need to be aware of that so I added the &lt;tt&gt;doc-impacting&lt;/tt&gt; label to this ticket as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
